summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 25489, entitled "An Ordinance authorizing and directing the City Engineer to incur an indebtedness against the General Fund in an amount not to exceed One Thousand Three Hundred Fifty Dollars ($1,350.00) on account of the coast and expense of the improvement of Whatcom Avenue by planking, as authorized by Ordinance No. 20401, creating Local Improvement District No. 1996," passed over Mayor's veto October 31st, 1910.
